In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 1 1/2 cups water.

While rice cooks, wash and dry all produce. Finely dice @Roma Tomato{1}. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Zest and quarter @Lime{1}. Core, deseed, and dice @Poblano Pepper{1} into 1/2-inch pieces. Pat @Chicken Breast Strips{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, scallion whites, and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with @salt{}. Add @Smoky Red Pepper Crema{4%tablespoon} to a separate small bowl. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until it reaches a drizzling consistency.

Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add poblano; cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{4-6%minutes}. Add another drizzle of oil, chicken, @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, and a pinch of salt. Cook until poblano is tender and chicken is browned all over, ~{2-4%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

> TIP: Add a splash of water if chicken begins to brown too quickly.

Pour in @water{1/2%cup}, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan. Add @Tex-Mex Paste{1%unit} and @Tomato Paste{1.5%ounce}; stir until fully incorporated. Bring to a simmer and cook until mixture has thickened and chicken is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Add a squeeze of lime juice to taste. Taste and season with @salt{} and @Pepper{}.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 1 cup water.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} and lime zest. Season with salt and pepper. Divide rice between shallow #bowls{}. Top with poblano and chicken mixture, salsa fresca, smoky red pepper crema, and scallion greens. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 2 TBSP butter.